2. Definitions

Authorized Use: Use by a natural person or legal entity which has obtained explicit written authorization from the Copyright Holder or a signed lawful engagement (e.g., SLA/SoW) from the owner of the target environment.

Malicious Use: Any use intended to interfere with, disrupt, exfiltrate data from, degrade, or destroy systems, networks or data without explicit written permission from the system owner.

Distribution: any public or private transfer, sale, publication, hosting (including public Git hosts), or re-licensing of the Software or Derivatives.

Derivative: any work that modifies, extends, incorporates or is derived from the Software.

